From 0a6fef7bf1f8b24e54bd7a4a26819566280298a4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Thu, 7 May 2026 14:04:27 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Phase B (rebuild): MultiDiffEditorWidget for the Diff
 sub-mode
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Replaces the per-file custom DiffEditorWidget stack with a single
embedded MultiDiffEditorWidget — same widget upstream's SCM source
control uses. Each PR file becomes a `IDocumentDiffItem` whose
original/modified models are resolved via
`ITextModelService.createModelReference` against:

  modified: file://${workspace.folderPath}/${path}
  original: krt-git://${workspace}/${baseSha}/${previousPath}

The modified `file://` URI runs through `IFileService` on the
workbench's normal file-loading path, so language extensions activate
naturally — rust-analyzer hover, goto-def, peek, find-references,
etc. all work in the diff. The original `krt-git://` URI is served by
Phase 8.6's existing content provider via `git show baseSha:path`,
read-only, no LSP (the base side rarely needs it).

Strict gate sits in the editor pane:
  - No workspace registered for (owner, repo) → CTA explaining and
    invoking `krt.workspace.add`.
  - Working tree not on PR head → CTA pointing at the Check Out
    button in the PR header (Phase 8.7's existing flow).
  - Both satisfied → mount the widget.

The gate keys off `isCheckedOut`, which `refreshCheckoutStatus`
already populates from `getHeadSha`. Hooked the post-flip path so
that going from "not checked out" → "checked out" (or back)
re-renders the diff sub-mode if active.

`KrtPrMultiDiff` (new file) wraps the widget, builds the model from
the PR's file list, and exposes `revealFile(modifiedUri,
originalUri)` for tree-row clicks. The widget self-virtualises and
self-scrolls; the host element's height is `min(70vh, 100vh - 200px)`
for a sensible viewport fit.

File tree on the left preserved — clicking a row reveals the
corresponding file inside the widget. Mark-reviewed UI temporarily
gone (the per-file checkbox lived in the deleted
`renderDiffFileSection`); Phase D adds it back via context menu on
the widget's per-file headers.

Storyboard chapter diff panel kept its Phase A placeholder — Phase
D rebuilds it on `KrtPrMultiDiff` scoped to chapter files.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
